The global remote sensing technology for agriculture market is expected to witness significant growth between 2020 and 2030. With the increasing adoption of technological solutions in the agriculture sector to enhance crop productivity and optimize resource utilization, remote sensing technology plays a crucial role in providing valuable insights to farmers. The market is segmented by offering into hardware, software, and services. Among these, the software segment is anticipated to witness rapid growth due to the rising demand for data analytics and visualization tools in agriculture. Additionally, the technology segment is divided into satellite remote sensing, airborne remote sensing, unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), and others. Satellite remote sensing is likely to hold a dominant position in the market as it offers wide coverage and cost-effective data acquisition capabilities. In terms of applications, the market is categorized into yield monitoring, soil monitoring, crop health monitoring, and others, where crop health monitoring is projected to experience substantial growth owing to the increasing need for early pest and disease detection.

